
################################
Updating Ephemeris Related Data
################################

Currently:  dir_list:   /data/mta4/Space_Weather/house_keeping/dir_list
            ephem_dir:  /data/mta4/Space_Weather/EPHEM/

dephem.pl   --- maintain a longterm archive of ephemeris data

    input:  /dsops/GOT/aux/DEPH.dir/DE<time stamp>.EPH

    output: <data_dir>/longterm/dephem.dat
            <data_dir>/longterm/DE/deph.<year><yday>

    function used:
        <bin_dir>/ephem_longterm.idl
        <bin_dir>/lephem_longterm.pro

ephem.pl    --- update gsme files

    input:  /dsops/GOT/aux/DEPH.dir/DE<time stamp>.EPH

    output: <data_dir>/PE.EPH
            <data_dir>/PE.EPH.gsme
            <data_dir>/PE.EPH.gsme_in
            <data_dir>/PE.EPH.gsme_in_Re
            <data_dir>/solun_eph.dat

    function used:
        <bin_dir>/ephem.idl
        <idl_dir>/read_ephemeris.pro
        <bin_dir>/lephem.pro
        <bin_dir>/solun_eph         --- compiled from solun_eph.f
        <bin_dir>/cocochan          --- complied from cocochan.f

gephem.pl   --- interpolate from the ephemeris file

    input:  <data_dir>/PE.EPH.dat
    output: <data_dir>/gephem.dat



Note:
    idl codes and fortran codes have hard coded paths. You need to 
    change them before use it. The fortran code need to be recomplie:

    f77 solun_eph.f -o solun_eph
    f77 cocochan.f /data/mta4/Space_Weather/geopack/geopack.f /data/mta4/Space_Weather/geopack/supple.f -o cocochan 


Cron Job
--------
han-v as mta

21 3 * * *  cd /data/mta4/Space_Weather/EPHEM/Scripts; /usr/bin/perl ephem.pl > /data/mta4/Space_Weather/Test_Logs/ephem_ephem.cron   2>&1
41 3 * * 0  cd /data/mta4/Space_Weather/EPHEM/Scripts; /usr/bin/perl dephem.pl> /data/mta4/Space_Weather/Test_Logs/ephem_dephem.cron  2>&1
*  * * * *  cd /data/mta4/Space_Weather/EPHEM/Scripts; /usr/bin/perl gephem.pl> /data/mta4/Space_Weather/Test_Logs/ephem_gephem.cron  2>&1

